{"entries":[{"caption":"Genotype–inheritance patterns in the SARA cohort. Stacked bars represent the number of patient–gene–variant configurations consistent with each inheritance mode, with individual patients potentially contributing more than one configuration in multigenic cases.","key":"fig-GenInher","order":{"number":3,"section":[2,0,0,0,0,0,0]}},{"caption":"Heatmap representation of the molecular annotation landscape of reported (A) and novel (B) variants, stratified by DNA variant type, protein-level effect, and ClinVar classification. Each cell corresponds to a distinct variant category, with values indicating counts of unique variants rather than patient-level observations. Marginal totals summarise the distribution of variants across DNA variant types and protein-level effect classes. Darker shading denotes higher variant counts.","key":"fig-com-rare-var","order":{"number":5,"section":[2,0,0,0,0,0,0]}},{"caption":"Recurrently implicated genes (frequency above 1% among genetically solved patients) in the SARA cohort. Genes with frequencies below 1% are reported in Supplementary Table S2.","key":"fig-frqgenes","order":{"number":2,"section":[2,0,0,0,0,0,0]}},{"caption":"Distribution of DNA variant types (A) and predicted protein-level effects (B) across all unique variants identified in the SARA cohort. SNPs and missense changes predominated, with a substantial contribution from loss-of-function variants, including frameshift and stop-gain alterations. Variants lacking an annotated protein-level consequence were classified as Unknown.","key":"fig-pies","order":{"number":4,"section":[2,0,0,0,0,0,0]}},{"caption":"Distribution of inherited retinal disease (IRD) diagnoses with a prevalence above 1% in the cohort. Bars indicate the number of patients, with percentages calculated among the genetically solved cases.","key":"fig-dxge1pct","order":{"number":1,"section":[2,0,0,0,0,0,0]}}],"headings":["introduction","results","discussion","methods","patients-cohort-and